29/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Balkan countries are to launch three tourism-related projects by the end of this year, according to a statement issued Friday (27 June) after a meeting between Bulgarian Deputy Economy Minister Dimiter Hadjinikolov and Yannis Patelis, president of the Greek National Tourism Organisation. 
The first project involves the release of a book presenting the traditional cuisine of the countries in the region, in line with the Memorandum for Understanding and Co-operation in Tourism of the Countries of South East Europe. 
The second project provides for the establishment of a joint Balkan rural tourism initiative. 
The third one envisions a workshop on the problems of cultural tourism in the region. 
(BTA - 27/06/03)
